An absolutely magnificent bizarre fraud that we  discussed a while back is =
that a Brazilian insurance company pretended that Warren Buffett had invest=
ed in its stock. This was very funny but made no real sense, because what h=
appened is:=09People believed them.=09The stock went up.=09Someone called B=
uffett=E2=80=99s company, Berkshire Hathaway Inc., to say =E2=80=9Cdid you?=
=E2=80=9D=09Berkshire said no.=09The stock went down.=09How was this going =
to end well?On Monday the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and feder=
al prosecutors=C2=A0brought fraud charges against Fernando Passos, =E2=80=
=9Cthe former executive vice president of finance and investor relations of=
 Brazilian reinsurance company IRB Brasil Resseguros S.A., for allegedly pl=
anting a false story with the media and disseminating false documents claim=
ing that Berkshire Hathaway Inc. had recently made a substantial investment=
