uary 2020, a Brazilian asset management firm that was short-selling IRB sto=
ck released a letter questioning the reliability and sustainability of IRB=
=E2=80=99s financial results (the =E2=80=9CShort-Seller Letter=E2=80=9D). =
=E2=80=A6In an attempt to bolster IRB=E2=80=99s stock price and reassure in=
vestors that IRB was a sound investment, Passos caused a false story to be =
