</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One problem with Elon Musk=E2=80=99s o=
ffer to buy Twitter Inc. for about $40 billion is that he does not have $40=
 billion. Of course he is very rich =E2=80=94=C2=A0the richest person in th=
e world, worth $260 billion by Bloomberg=E2=80=99s estimate =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
but most of that money is tied up in the stock of Tesla Inc., SpaceX, the B=
oring Co., etc., and it is not obvious that he would want to sell enough of=
 those things to buy a new thing. Nor is it obvious that anyone else would =
want to give him $40 billion to buy Twitter, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/27430244.257597/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29t=
LzIwMjIvNC8xNC8yMzAyNTM0My9lbG9uLW11c2stdHdpdHRlci10YWtlb3Zlci10ZWQtdGFsay1=
xdW90ZS1zdG9jay1idXlvdXQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa4ea90c0" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">given t=
hat</a> he sees Twitter as =E2=80=9Cnot a way to make money=E2=80=9D and do=
es not =E2=80=9Ccare about the economics at all.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Another problem with Musk=E2=80=99s offer to buy Twitter is =
that, if you ask him where the money is coming from, he says things <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27430244.257597/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9saXZlY292ZXJhZ2UvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXR3aXR0ZXIvY2FyZC9lbG9uLW11=
c2stc2F5cy1oZS1vZmZlcmVkLXRvLWJ1eS10d2l0dGVyLWJlY2F1c2UtaXQtcy1iZWNvbWUtZGU=
tZmFjdG8tdG93bi1zcXVhcmUtLWp2TWxrUm5IZzFOSUlnUTZwSFlH/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB7cb0819e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">like</a> =E2=80=9CI have sufficient assets=E2=80=9D <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27430244.257597/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTQvbXVzay1zYX=
lzLWhlLXMtbm90LXN1cmUtaGUtbGwtc3VjY2VlZC13aXRoLXR3aXR0ZXItYWNxdWlzaXRpb24_Y=
21waWQ9QkJEMDQyMDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5l=
d3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDIwJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBaf8a4e83" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;"> and</a> =E2=80=9CI am not sure that I wil=
l actually be able to acquire it,=E2=80=9D which do not inspire confidence =
that he has actually thought about raising the money.</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">A third problem with Musk=E2=80=99s offer to buy Twitter is that=
 in 2018 he mused about taking Tesla Inc. private for about $70 billion. =
=E2=80=9CFunding secured,=E2=80=9D he said, in an infamous tweet. It <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27430244.257597/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDktMjgvbXVzay1zLXR=
lc2xhLWZ1bi1kb2VzLW5vdC1hbXVzZS1zZWM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQyMDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdX=
RtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDIwJnV0b=
V9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcdb3ea7d" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> tur=
ned out</a> that he had had a single casual conversation=C2=A0with represen=
tatives of a Saudi sovereign wealth fund in which they did not discuss the =
price of the deal or how much money the Saudis were willing to invest; ulti=
mately Musk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/274302=
44.257597/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtM=
TAtMDEvdGVzbGEtd2lsbC10cnktdG8tYmUtbW9yZS1ub3JtYWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQyMDIyX01P=
TkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm0=
9MjIwNDIwJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB24b5b0fd=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> settled fraud charges</a> with the Securities and Exchange Commi=
ssion over this tweet. So the answer to the question =E2=80=9Cmight Elon Mu=
sk have made an offer to take a large public company private, at a cost of =
tens of billions of dollars, without giving any real thought to where the m=
oney would come from?=E2=80=9D is =E2=80=9Cabsolutely yes, and he=E2=80=99s=
 done it before.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">All of these prob=
lems mean that, if you are a Twitter shareholder and Musk says =E2=80=9CI a=
m going to buy Twitter for $54.20 per share,=E2=80=9D you might not believe=
 him. =E2=80=9CShow me the money,=E2=80=9D you might reasonably say. And in=
 fact, when Musk did publicly announce his bid, <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27430244.257597/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTUvc3VyZS1lbG9uLW11c2stbWlnaHQtYnV5=
LXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQyMDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1=
fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDIwJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dW=
Zm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8a15fdc9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the stock price=C2=A0<em>drop=
ped</em></a>, closing at $45.08 on the day his bid became public. <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27430244.257597/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIy=
MDQ1NjQxL3RtMjIxMjc0OGQxX3NjMTNkYS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB44f0191e" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">Musk=E2=80=99s proposal</a> was contingent on =E2=80=9Ccompletion o=
f anticipated financing,=E2=80=9D and that is a big if.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">Similarly, if you are Twitter=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>board</em>, y=
